const gpRodsAlgorithmTopic: LibraryTopic = {
  id: 'gp-rods-algorithm',
  subjectId: 'microbiology',
  subspecialtyId: 'microbiology-gram-positive',
  name: 'GP Rods Algorithm',
  slug: 'gp-rods-algorithm',
  description: 'Spore-forming vs non-spore, aerobic vs anaerobic, identification',
  content: {
    concept: `# Gram-Positive Rods - Identification Algorithm

## Step 1: Spore Formation

**Spore-forming** → Bacillus or Clostridium
**Non-spore-forming** → Listeria, Corynebacterium, Lactobacillus, etc.

---

## Spore-Forming GP Rods

### Step 2: Oxygen Requirements

**Aerobic/Facultative** → **BACILLUS**
**Obligate Anaerobic** → **CLOSTRIDIUM**

### Bacillus Species

| Species | Motility | Hemolysis | Capsule | Disease |
|---------|----------|-----------|---------|---------|
| B. anthracis | **Non-motile** | γ (none) | + (polypeptide) | Anthrax |
| B. cereus | Motile | β | - | Food poisoning |

**Key**: B. anthracis is NON-motile, NON-hemolytic

### Clostridium Species

| Species | Spore Shape | Key Feature | Disease |
|---------|-------------|-------------|---------|
| C. tetani | Terminal (drumstick) | Tetanospasmin | Tetanus |
| C. botulinum | Subterminal | Botulinum toxin | Botulism |
| C. perfringens | Central/subterminal | Non-motile, lecithinase | Gas gangrene |
| C. difficile | Subterminal oval | Toxin A&B | Pseudomembranous colitis |

**Unique**: C. perfringens is the only NON-MOTILE Clostridium

---

## Non-Spore-Forming GP Rods

### Key Organisms

| Organism | Morphology | Key Tests | Disease |
|----------|------------|-----------|---------|
| **Listeria** | Small coccobacillus | Tumbling motility (25°C), cold growth, β-hemolytic | Meningitis, pregnancy |
| **Corynebacterium** | Club-shaped, Chinese letters | Metachromatic granules, Elek test | Diphtheria |
| **Lactobacillus** | Long rods | Part of normal flora | Non-pathogenic |
| **Erysipelothrix** | Slender rods | H₂S production | Erysipeloid |

---

## Branching GP Rods

| Organism | Acid-fast | Aerobe | Sulfur Granules | Disease |
|----------|-----------|--------|-----------------|---------|
| **Nocardia** | Weakly + | Yes | No | Lung, brain abscess |
| **Actinomyces** | - | No (anaerobe) | Yes | Lumpy jaw |

---

## Quick Reference Algorithm

\`\`\`
Gram-Positive Rods
    │
    ├─ SPORE-FORMING
    │       │
    │       ├─ Aerobic → BACILLUS
    │       │       ├─ Non-motile, Non-hemolytic → B. anthracis
    │       │       └─ Motile, β-hemolytic → B. cereus
    │       │
    │       └─ Anaerobic → CLOSTRIDIUM
    │               ├─ Drumstick spore → C. tetani
    │               ├─ Non-motile, lecithinase + → C. perfringens
    │               └─ Subterminal spore → C. botulinum, C. difficile
    │
    ├─ NON-SPORE-FORMING
    │       │
    │       ├─ Tumbling motility, cold growth → Listeria
    │       ├─ Chinese letters, granules → Corynebacterium
    │       └─ Normal flora, non-pathogenic → Lactobacillus
    │
    └─ BRANCHING
            ├─ Weakly acid-fast, aerobic → Nocardia
            └─ Anaerobic, sulfur granules → Actinomyces
\`\`\``,
    
    keyPoints: [
      'First division: Spore-forming vs Non-spore-forming',
      'Bacillus: Aerobic spore-former; Clostridium: Anaerobic spore-former',
      'B. anthracis is NON-motile (unlike B. cereus)',
      'C. perfringens is NON-motile (unlike other Clostridia)',
      'Listeria: Tumbling motility at 25°C, grows at 4°C',
      'Corynebacterium: Chinese letter arrangement, metachromatic granules',
